    <h2 id="purchasing">Purchasing Premium</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Open BudgetBaby and tap any locked Premium feature, or go to <strong>Settings → Premium</strong>.</li>
      <li>Review the monthly ($7.99) and annual ($69.99) options. The annual plan saves approximately 27% and works out to $5.83 per month.</li>
      <li>Tap your preferred plan. Apple will confirm the purchase with Face ID, Touch ID, or your Apple ID password.</li>
      <li>Premium activates immediately. No restart is required.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      BudgetBaby uses RevenueCat to manage subscription entitlements. RevenueCat verifies your
      App Store receipt and tells the app which features to unlock. We never see or store your
      payment information.
    </p>

    <h2 id="restoring-purchases">Restoring purchases</h2>
    <p>
      If you reinstall BudgetBaby, switch to a new device, or find that Premium is not showing
      after purchase, use Restore Purchases:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Premium</strong>.</li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Restore Purchases</strong>.</li>
      <li>Sign in with the Apple ID that originally purchased Premium if prompted.</li>
      <li>Premium will be restored within a few seconds as RevenueCat re-verifies your receipt.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="doc-tip">
      <strong>Most common reason restore fails:</strong> You are signed in to the App Store with a different Apple ID than the one used to purchase. Go to Settings → (your name) → Media and Purchases to confirm which Apple ID the device is using. If you have multiple Apple IDs and are unsure which made the purchase, check your email for the App Store receipt.
    </div>
    <p>
      If restore still does not work after confirming the Apple ID, contact
      <a href="mailto:support@babyblocks.io">support@babyblocks.io</a> with your order number
      or the Apple ID used to purchase. Include your app version from Settings → About.
    </p>

    <h2 id="cancelling">Cancelling</h2>
    <p>
      BudgetBaby subscriptions are managed entirely by Apple. We cannot cancel a subscription on
      your behalf, process a cancellation ourselves, or tell you the exact billing date.
      All subscription management lives in iOS Settings.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on your iPhone (not BudgetBaby Settings).</li>
      <li>Tap your name at the top of the screen.</li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Subscriptions</strong>.</li>
      <li>Find and tap <strong>BudgetBaby</strong> in the list.</li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Cancel Subscription</strong> and confirm.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Cancellation takes effect at the end of your current billing period. You retain Premium
      access until that date. After it expires, the free tier limits are re-applied.
      Your data is not deleted when you cancel.
    </p>
    <div class="doc-tip">
      <strong>If you do not see BudgetBaby in your subscription list,</strong> you may be signed in with a different Apple ID, or the subscription may have already lapsed. Check by signing in to the Apple ID you used to purchase at appleid.apple.com.
    </div>

    <h2 id="refunds">Refunds</h2>
    <p>
      Apple processes all refunds. We cannot issue refunds directly or override Apple's decision.
    </p>
    <p>
      To request a refund, visit
      <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">reportaproblem.apple.com</a>,
      sign in with the Apple ID used to purchase, find the BudgetBaby charge, and select
      "Request a refund." Choose the most appropriate reason from Apple's list.
      Apple typically responds within a few days.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you believe you were charged in error or have a billing dispute that Apple's process
      is not resolving, email <a href="mailto:support@babyblocks.io">support@babyblocks.io</a>.
      We will assist with the Apple dispute process as best we can, though the final refund
      decision is always Apple's.
    </p>
